  "prompt": "What is the average salary of an MBA graduate in India?",
  "response": "As of the most recent data, the average salary of an MBA graduate in India can vary significantly based on several factors such as the industry, job role, experience, and the institute from which the degree is obtained. Typically, graduates from top business schools like the Indian Institutes of Management (IIMs) or other prestigious institutions may see higher average salaries, often ranging from \u20b910 lakhs to \u20b925 lakhs per annum. For MBA graduates from other institutes, the average salary might range from \u20b94 lakhs to \u20b910 lakhs per annum. \n\nHowever, it's important to note that these figures are subject to change over time and economic conditions, so for the most accurate and up-to-date information, consulting recent placement reports and salary surveys from reputable sources is recommended.",
